Package view

Class ToDoView

java.lang.Object
javafx.application.Application
view.ToDoView
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.util.Observer
public class ToDoView
extends javafx.application.Application
implements java.util.Observer
Uses javafx GUI to implement a visual representation of the ToDo list and allows for user interactions such as adding/removing tasks, adding/ removing lists, marking/unmarking task importance/completion, changing background colors of each list individually, and traversing multiple ToDo lists changing sort order, renaming tasks/lists, hiding/showing completed tasks. This is done by communicating to a controller object and using event handlers.
Author:
Henry Do, Gerry Guardiola, Mauricio Brooks, Xin Li
